# Angular 21 + PrimeNG + Tailwind Project Rules

## Project Stack
- Angular 21 (Standalone Components)
- PrimeNG 18+ (UI Components)
- Tailwind CSS 4+ (Styling)
- TypeScript 5.7+
- Signals-based State Management

## Core Principles

### 1. Component Architecture
- ALWAYS use standalone components (no NgModules)
- ALWAYS use Angular Signals for reactive state
- ALWAYS use OnPush change detection strategy
- NEVER use zone.js-based change detection patterns
- Use `inject()` function for dependency injection over constructor injection

### 2. Angular Signals Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Use signals for component state
import { Component, signal, computed, effect } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-example',
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
})
export class ExampleComponent {
  // Use signal() for mutable state
  count = signal(0);
  
  // Use computed() for derived state
  doubleCount = computed(() => this.count() * 2);
  
  // Use effect() for side effects
  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      console.log('Count changed:', this.count());
    });
  }
  
  increment() {
    this.count.update(c => c + 1);
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG: Don't use traditional properties
export class WrongComponent {
  count = 0; // Don't do this
  
  increment() {
    this.count++; // Don't do this
  }
}
